{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2896", "repo": "rails", "body": "Hi, thanks for the patch.\r\n\r\nRather than adding a `column_name` param to `references_eager_loaded_table?`, I would prefer that we pass through the exact SQL used by `count`. E.g., I would change the method signature to this:\r\n\r\n``` ruby\r\ndef references_eager_loaded_table?(sql = to_sql)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd then change `count` to pass through the appropriate sql. Does that sound workable?", "_id": {"$oid": "523f9727bd354364b9019371"}, "issue_id": 2896, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2043490", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2896#issuecomment-2043490", "updated_at": "2011-09-08T19:14:37Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "login": "jonleighton", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-09-08T19:14:23Z", "id": 2043490, "owner": "rails"}
